    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Equations Homogeneous (i.e., of the same power throughout) in x and y."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Rule. Make the substitution $y = vx$ and separate the variables."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Example 14.--Solve the equation $(x+y) \frac{dy}{dx} = xy$."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Let $y = vx,$ then"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "$y' = v + x \frac{dv}{dx}$  ... (1)"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Now"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Substituting for $y$,"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "$(x + vx) \bigg(v + x \frac{dv}{dx}\bigg) = vx \times x$."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Separating the variables, and integrating,"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "or $log(1 - v) = - log C + K$ (the substitution being $K = - \frac{1}{x}$)"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "or $log(1 - v) = K$ and"
      },
      {
        "type": "equation",
        "latex": "v = 1 - e^{K}.",
        "description": "This shows the relationship between $v$ and an exponential function."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Linear Equations of the Second Order."
